| ✅ |\n\n**Scope creep:** The quality loop now calls `comment_issue` on convergence — not listed in the implementation tasks. The prior test guarding against any `comment_issue` in the quality loop was weakened to accommodate this. Low-risk, but undeclared.\n\n---\n\n## Part 2 — Code Review\n\n### 🔴 Critical — Multi-line `repeat_issues` silently truncated\n\n**File:** `implement-issue-orchestrator.sh` (quality loop convergence block)\n\n`read -r repeat_ratio repeat_issues` reads **one line only**. The jq expression joins repeating issues with `\\n- `, producing a multi-line string. For 2+ repeating issues, only the first issue is captured; the rest are silently discarded.\n\n**Fix:** Use two separate jq invocations instead of packing both values into one line:\n```bash\nrepeat_ratio=$(printf '%s' \"$review_result\" | jq '... ratio calculation ...' 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\nrepeat_issues=$(printf '%s' \"$review_result\" | jq -r '... issues list ...' 2>/dev/null || echo '')\n```\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Important — AC4 partial: stage names missing from cascade warning\n\nThe warning logs the count (`$_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS`) but not which stages timed out. `$stage_name` is in scope at the point of increment and should be accumulated.\n\n**Fix:**\n```bash\n_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES=\"${_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES:+$_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES, }$stage_name\"\n(( _CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS++ )) || true\nif (( _CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS >= 2 )); then\n    log_warn \"Cascade timeout detected: $_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS consecutive stage(s)\" \\\n        \"timed out: $_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES. Consider increasing timeout or reducing complexity.\"\nfi\n```\nReset `_TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES=\"\"` alongside every `_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS=0` reset.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ What's Done Well\n\n- Soft exit (AC3): `loop_complete=true; break` cleanly mirrors the quality loop pattern. `set_final_state \"test_convergence_soft_exit\"` naming is clear and distinguishes from hard failures.\n- `.result` timeout fallback reuses the same `select(.is_error == false and .result != null)` jq pattern consistently with the rest of the file.\n- `_CONSECUTIVE_TIMEOUTS` resets are thorough — fires on success, non-timeout error, and schema-not-found, preventing false positives.\n- `(( expr )) || true` idiom is correctly applied for arithmetic in `set -e` environments.\n- Test coverage is extensive (10 new behavioral cases in stage-runner alone), including the important recovery path (counter stays 0 when initial timeout recovers via structured output).\n- Commit messages are precise and reference the specific line numbers from the issue.","issues":[{"severity":"major","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","description":"Multi-line repeat_issues silently truncated: `read -r repeat_ratio repeat_issues < <(jq ... join(\"\\n- \") ...)` reads only the first line. When 2+ issues repeat, all but the first are discarded. Use two separate jq calls instead of packing both values into a single packed line format."},{"severity":"major","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":905,"description":"AC4 partially unmet: cascade timeout warning logs count but not stage names. AC4 spec requires 'warning log entry with timeout count and stage names'. $stage_name is in scope at the increment point — accumulate it in a parallel _TIMED_OUT_STAGE_NAMES variable and include it in the log_warn message."},{"severity":"minor","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","description":"Undeclared scope creep: quality loop gains a comment_issue call on convergence that was not in the implementation tasks. The prior regression test guarding against any comment_issue in the quality loop was weakened to accommodate this. Acknowledge explicitly in the PR description or revert to match the issue tasks."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"e23517f7-da8c-4f26-83b0-975ae602d7d6"}
